    "http://ogp.me/ns#title": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Pipes and Strings - Brantford Symphony Orchestra"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "The glorious organ at St. Andrew's will feature one of Canada's foremost recitalists, organist Ian Sadler. Currently the Organist at Toronto's St. James Anglican Cathedral, Ian's list of accomplishments and successes as an Organist and a Choir Director place him in the top tier of Canada's outstanding musicians. With the BSO strings and horns, Ian will perform Josef Rheinberger's sumptuous Concerto #1 in F Major. The organ console will be front and centre, for you to see Ian in action and you will be amazed! The BSO strings will be featured on their own with deliciously romantic music, to fill out a substantial and satisfying classical music concert."
      },
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Guest Artist Ian Sadler\n\nThe glorious organ at St. Andrew's will feature one of Canada's foremost recitalists, organist Ian Sadler. Currently the Organist at Toronto's St. James Anglican Cathedral, Ian's list of accomplishments and successes as an Organist and a Choir Director place him in the top tier of Canada's outstanding musicians. With the BSO strings"
      }
    ],
