    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Long before the Saxophone became associated with jazz and wind bands, it was considered primarily as an instrument along “serious” lines such as oboes or clarinets. Capable of long, deep melodies, or flashy and quick virtuosity, it is a remarkably versatile instrument, fitting in easily with many musical styles and approaches. Alexander Glazunov’s lavish Saxophone"
      }
